item.title: Hi im new working on models
item.dc:creator: @Java_Is_My_Bitch2 Java Is My Bitch
item.description:
@Java_Is_My_Bitch2 wrote:

Blender’s a little harder to get a grasp on but when you do your model will be 50% better than what you could ever do in meta in 50% less time than in meta. Although meta is a more simple point and click modeling program. Blender has more complicated, more neat tools, while on the other hand meta has simple, easy to learn although less efficient tools. Anyways, the choice is yours.

I use Metasequioa because its what I’ve learned to use from this community. Its great for beginners as its a very easy to grasp program, but there are many others that you could use. But if you plan on making models for RSPS, use Metasequioa or Blender.
